{"type":"message","id":"06653382","parentId":"fa745f97","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:52:10.835Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"191,683 lines of log output. The pipeline is actively working on audio file copying. Now I need to set up a monitoring loop - checking every ~30 seconds for progress and whether Unity is still running. Let me use a script that loops every 30 seconds.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_mYSaZOKYXxTOJKzpLRQj7242","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -NoProfile -Command @\"\n$logFile = 'E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log'\n$unityPid = 10528\n\n# Monitor loop: check every 30 seconds\nwhile ($true) {\n    Start-Sleep -Seconds 30\n    \n    # Check if Unity is still running\n    $proc = Get-Process -Id $unityPid -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    if (-not $proc) {\n        Write-Host \"UNITY_PROCESS_EXITED\"\n        break\n    }\n    \n    # Show progress from log\n    $lineCount = (Get-Content $logFile | Measure-Object -Line).Lines\n    $last5 = Get-Content $logFile -Tail 5 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    \n    # Look for progress indicators\n    $progress = Get-Content $logFile | Select-String -Pattern \"(Building|Build|完成|成功|Error|error|Exception|Finished|Upload|CDN|上传)\" -Tail 3 -SimpleMatch:$false -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n    \n    Write-Host \"=== 监控报告 ===\"\n    Write-Host \"时间: $(Get-Date -Format 'HH:mm:ss')\"\n    Write-Host \"日志行数: $lineCount\"\n    Write-Host \"最近关键行:\"\n    if ($progress) {\n        $progress | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  $($_.Line)\" }\n    }\n    Write-Host \"最后5行:\"\n    $last5 | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  $_\" }\n    Write-Host \"==================\"\n}\n\n# Parse the final log state after Unity exits\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== 最终日志分析 ===\"\n$last20 = Get-Content $logFile -Tail 20\nWrite-Host \"最后20行:\"\n$last20 | ForEach-Object { Write-Host \"  $_\" }\n\"@","ti